Why This Document Exists
========================

The Inform compiler and standard library continue to evolve, 
introducing new features and functionalities. As the Inform Designer's 
Manual becomes increasingly outdated, its proprietary nature makes it 
challenging to update and adapt the documentation to reflect these 
changes. This inability to update the documentation can lead to 
confusion and frustration for users, especially newcomers, who may 
struggle to utilize the latest features without accurate and 
up-to-date documentation. The community has resorted to publishing 
change logs and supplementary materials. While helpful, this approach 
leads to fragmentation of the documentation and makes it difficult for 
users to find the necessary information. A single, up-to-date manual 
that freely allows changes enables the community to have control over 
its documentation by collaboratively updating and maintaining it, 
fostering a sense of community ownership, avoiding fragmentation, and 
ensuring its accuracy and relevance in providing a centralized and 
reliable source of information for all users as Inform 6 evolves.

