    values to avoid unexpected behavior and potential errors.

    Comments: Use comments to explain the purpose and usage of global 
    variables, especially for those accessed from different parts of 
    your code. This improves code understanding and facilitates 
    collaboration with other developers.

    Memory limitations: Be mindful of memory limitations when working 
    with large numbers of global variables or arrays. Consider 
    alternative data structures or optimization techniques if 
    necessary.

    Side effects: Be cautious when modifying global variables within 
    functions, as this can lead to unintended side effects and make 
    debugging more difficult. Consider using local variables or 
    passing arguments by value if possible.

Variable Types and Initialization

