    and concise to improve readability and avoid potential errors. Use 
    meaningful variable and function names, and avoid overly complex 
    expressions.

    Specificity: Define rules with specific conditions to avoid 
    unintended side effects and ensure that they trigger only when 
    desired.

    Efficiency: Consider the efficiency of your rules, especially when 
    using complex conditions or actions that might be evaluated 
    frequently. Optimize your code where necessary to avoid 
    performance issues.

    Organization: Organize your rules logically within object and room 
    definitions. Group related rules together and use comments to 
