    characters).

    substring(string, start, end): Extracts a substring from the 
    string, starting at the start index and ending at the end index 
    (exclusive).

    compare(string1, string2): Compares two strings and returns a 
    negative, zero, or positive value depending on whether string1 is 
    less than, equal to, or greater than string2.

    uppercase(string): Converts the string to uppercase.

    lowercase(string): Converts the string to lowercase.

These functions allow you to perform various operations on strings, 
such as extracting specific characters, comparing strings for 
equality, or changing their case.

