Example

Here's an example of how to use global variables, object properties, 
and attributes to manage persistent data and game state:

    Global player_health = 100;
    Global has_key = false;

    Object -> door "wooden door"
    with
        locked true,
        ...
    ;

    after [;
        Take: if (noun == key) {
            has_key = true;
        }

        Unlock: if (noun == door && has_key) {
            door.locked = false;
            print "You unlock the door.";
        }
    ];

This code uses global variables to track the player's health and 
whether they have the key. The door object has a locked property that 
