Switches: Object Properties for Conditional Behavior

Switches are similar to flags but are implemented as object 
properties. They are used to control the behavior of individual 
objects based on their boolean state. For example:

    Openable objects: A door object might have a locked switch that 
    determines whether it can be opened or not.

    Switchable objects: A lamp object might have an on switch that 
