Chapter 12: Extending Inform 6

Chapter 12.1: Using and Creating Extensions

Extensions are pre-built libraries or modules that add new features 
and capabilities to your Inform 6 games. They can provide a wide range 
of functionality, from advanced text formatting and menu systems to 
complex gameplay mechanics and world model extensions.

This sub-chapter will offer a comprehensive exploration of using and 
creating extensions in Inform 6, covering finding and installing 
extensions, integrating them into your project, understanding 
extension structure, creating your own extensions, and best practices 
for leveraging extensions to enhance the functionality and complexity 
of your interactive fiction games.

Finding and Installing Extensions: Expanding Your Toolkit

The Inform 6 community has created a vast collection of extensions 
that are available for download. Here are some sources for finding 
extensions:

    Inform 6 website: The official Inform 6 website maintains a list 
    of extensions and provides links to their download locations.

    Interactive Fiction Archive: The Interactive Fiction Archive (IF 
