Once you have found an extension you want to use, follow the 
installation instructions provided by the extension's documentation. 
This typically involves downloading the extension files and placing 
them in the appropriate directory within your Inform 6 installation or 
project folder.

Integrating Extensions into Your Project: Adding Functionality

To integrate an extension into your Inform 6 project, you need to 
include its header file in your source code using the Include 
directive. For example:

    Include "Menus.h";

This code includes the "Menus.h" extension, which provides a pre-built 
