    during the integration process.

    Modularity: Use extensions to add specific functionality without 
    bloating your core game code. This helps maintain a clean and 
    organized codebase.

Understanding Extension Structure: A Look Inside

Extensions are typically structured as Inform 6 source code files that 
define objects, classes, routines, and other elements. Understanding 
the structure of extensions can help you integrate them more 
effectively and troubleshoot any issues that might arise.

Here are some common elements found in extensions:

    Header file: The header file usually contains the Include 
